00:01:03.279 --> 00:01:11.440
these three ideals. So we want basically good and cheap healthcare whenever we need it, right? So

00:01:11.440 --> 00:01:20.239
we have the affordability, availability and quality of healthcare. Unfortunately it's actually quite

00:01:20.239 --> 00:01:26.120
impossible to have all three of these ideals. So there's always a trade-off between them. And

00:01:26.120 --> 00:01:31.720
at the Dutch Healthcare Authority we are often looking at this impossible triangle through a

00:01:31.720 --> 00:01:40.400
more economic lens. So as you know healthcare often boils down to money. It does. So things

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:45.519
that we are on the lookout for are things like fraud or misuse of healthcare funds,

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:53.400
unexpected bankruptcies, things like that. And we use data and dashboarding to monitor this and

00:01:53.400 --> 00:01:59.959
intervene where necessary. But to reintroduce a little bit of complexity because this really is

00:01:59.959 --> 00:02:06.919
too simple, we are not the only regulator in the Netherlands that deals with healthcare. So the

00:02:06.919 --> 00:02:14.679
landscape looks more like this. So we are somewhere in there and actually there are more than this

00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:22.000
because some of the regulating tasks are on the municipal level. So basically any municipality

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:28.279
has regulating tasks. And as you can see all of these regulators are basically optimizing for

00:02:28.279 --> 00:02:34.839
the same problem, right? Again the good and cheap healthcare whenever we need it. Yeah, so same

00:02:34.839 --> 00:02:41.919
problem. Mostly the same data and mostly the same needs in terms of dashboarding, which is why we

00:02:41.919 --> 00:02:48.880
decided at some point to build a shiny dashboard. We are in the shiny session after all. And share

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:54.479
that with other regulators. So the three organizations over there came together and

00:02:54.479 --> 00:03:00.320
decided to build a shiny dashboard. And then the idea was to share that with as many other regulators

00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:10.720
as possible. That worked out pretty nicely until this happened. So turned out we were sharing data

00:03:10.839 --> 00:03:16.679
with regulators that we were not allowed to share. Because all of these regulators have

00:03:16.679 --> 00:03:21.759
different laws, different jurisdictions, making things really, really complicated. And what we

00:03:21.759 --> 00:03:30.080
were doing was technically not allowed. Yeah, so we weren't allowed to continue with that. So we

00:03:30.080 --> 00:03:35.360
had to decide either build a different dashboard for each different type of user, which is horrible,

00:03:35.479 --> 00:03:43.720
or yeah, kick people off the platform, which is also horrible. But that's what we did. So we kicked

00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:49.440
a lot of users out and only the ones that we were actually allowed to share the whole dashboard with

00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:54.679
stayed on. But yeah, that kind of defeated the purpose of the dashboard because we wanted to

00:03:54.679 --> 00:04:00.720
share healthcare information with all the other regulators, right? So we had to go back to the

00:04:00.720 --> 00:04:08.240
drawing board and come up with something better, which is where the modular design comes in. So we

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:12.960
thought, well, if we cannot share the whole dashboard or the dashboard as a whole, why not

00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:19.279
just cut it up into pieces? And then for each of the pieces, or let's say modules, we can decide

00:04:19.279 --> 00:04:27.720
with whom we can share that. So that should give us enough control to be compliant with the privacy

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:34.559
law. So it would look something like this. You have groups of modules and groups of users based

00:04:34.559 --> 00:04:39.239
on the sensitivity of the data and based on the different laws and who gets access to what. And

00:04:39.239 --> 00:04:47.519
then it's a matter of just mapping these two groups. So managing user access and GDPR

00:04:47.519 --> 00:04:54.720
compliancy was the main reason to go with a modular setup. The second has to do with spaghetti

