00:07:37.640 --> 00:07:43.760
specific modules for the actual content, right? You can reuse them, but, you know, they're a bit

00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:53.200
more specific. So with this setup, we could actually link that to access control and decide

00:07:53.200 --> 00:07:59.000
who gets to see what. But we also had to do something about the layout of the dashboard.

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:03.239
Because if you imagine you have the same layout for all of your users, but some of the modules

00:08:03.239 --> 00:08:09.359
are not accessible, either you log in and you see a giant access denied message in certain places on

00:08:09.359 --> 00:08:14.239
your page, or maybe there are these giant gaping holes where apparently there was a module, but

